FBIS4-35333 "drnes104_j_94048" FBIS-NES-94-104 Daily Report 29 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Tahir Visits Hospital, Says Troops in Good Spirits Tahir Visits Hospital, Says Troops in Good Spirits EA2905193894 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1700 GMT 29 May 94 EA2905193894 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1700 GMT 29 May 94 Arabic BFN [Text] Brother Staff Brigadier General Haytham Qasim Tahir, the defense minister, carried out an inspection tour this afternoon at the Ba Suhayb Military Hospital, during which he visited a number of those wounded during the war imposed by 'Ali Abdallah Salih on our people and homeland. During his visit to the wounded, and his inspection of the hospital, the brother defense minister gave instructions on the care to be extended to the wounded. He gave instructions that the hospital be supplied with everything it required to enable it to provide the sick and wounded with optimal services. Following his visit to the Ba Suhayb Military Hospital, Staff Brigadier General Haytham Qasim Tahir replied to questions posed to him by a number of correspondents. He told them that the Armed Forces of the Democratic Republic of Yemen had won a number of victories on all battlefronts, and that all the fighters enjoyed high morale in repulsing the aggressive forces of the bloody al-Ahmar clan.
